== Early life <small>(1898-1916)</small> ==

=== Birth and family background <small>(1898-1901)</small> ===
{{PAGENAME}} was born on February 26, 1883 in Jerusalem, Ottoman Empire to Baila Levi. His mother was unemployed.

=== Childhood <small>(1901-1916)</small> ===
Growing up, Yosefs mother married Omri Dahan in 1901 and she also became a firefighter the same year. At 15 Yosef joined the astronomy club and became treasurer, he also went to space camp. His half-sister was born in 1916.

== Adult years <small>(1916-1952)</small> ==
As an adult, {{PAGENAME}} Emigrated to Tampa, USA in 1916 and changed his name to Joseph Levy. His half-brother was born in 1918 and Josephs second half-sister was born in 1920 and became a police officer in 1932

== Post retirement (1952-1994) ==
After retirement in 1952, Levy saved someone's life in 1958. He died in 1994, aged 96.

== Personal life ==
In 1929 he married Avery Gray and had 9 children with her.

